name: Jumpingjack 64
overview: Jumpingjack 64 is a game similar in some ways to the game Jumping Jack released by CP Verlag 7 years later, albeit a bit more primitive. Try to reach the top of the screen. The game was ironically also released as Jumping Jack, but only in Italy. The game was developed by Paul Burger and published in the following: As Jumpingjack 64 in COMPUTE! 1983/05 (Issue #36) and by Dutch based Courbois Software in Courbois Software #6409 (although the game kept the English title screen in the Dutch release) As Jumping Jack in Paper Soft 1984/05, and also in Jackson Soft Oro #7
